To implement the soft-delete functionality using the `is_deleted` column for both the **Style Library** and the **Orders**, please follow these instructions.

### 1. Run this SQL in Supabase
Run this query in your Supabase SQL Editor to add the required columns and set the defaults.

```sql
-- 1. Update Style Library table
ALTER TABLE style_library ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS is_deleted BOOLEAN DEFAULT false;
UPDATE style_library SET is_deleted = false WHERE is_deleted IS NULL;

-- 2. Update Orders table (migrate from 'deleted' to 'is_deleted')
ALTER TABLE orders ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS is_deleted BOOLEAN DEFAULT false;

-- If you have an old 'deleted' column, migrate the data:
DO $$ 
BEGIN 
    IF EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM information_schema.columns WHERE table_name='orders' AND column_name='deleted') THEN
        UPDATE orders SET is_deleted = deleted;
    END IF;
END $$;

UPDATE orders SET is_deleted = false WHERE is_deleted IS NULL;
```

### 2. Code Updates
I have updated the backend service to use `is_deleted` for all queries and added the missing delete button to the main rows in both dashboards.

